flowRoot.flowPara: The graph on the right shows the variation in the circuit seen in monte carlo simulations with all resistors set to a tolerance of 1%.

The tolerance can be investigated using RS/1. Using the distrib command it is possible to estimate the response of the model created by RS/1 to describe the circuit. Initially, as RC is calculated for each experiment the circuit will always be balanced - which does not reflect the true situation. It would be possible to characterise this response in RS/1 by adding it as a response and recreating the model.

However, in order to optimise the tolerances of the resistors it was decided to create an external Monte Carlo simulator and use the output of this in RS/1 to create a model - and then use this to optimise the tolerances for accuracy.
